    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Those sound like good starts. I've heard some people say that in those areas, the schools are better because the neighborhoods are more \"homogenous\" and there's less social tension or outside influence. Is that actually true? Like, do you think staying in one of those areas helps keep the schools higher-achieving and the environment more stable compared to more diverse or urban areas?",
